15 Mark Question | Sum of digits in a String.
Write a Java program that reads a string containing a mix of letters (in any case) and digits.
Calculate the sum of all digits in the string, following these rules:

If the sum of digits is 15 or less, print the sum.
If the sum is greater than 15, or if no digits are found, print "No Digit Found".
Examples
Input: "GTAen9y4"

Output: 13
Input: "pue8QM9"

Output: "No Digit Found"
Input: "helloWorld"

Output: "No Digit Found"
Write the code in the public class Solution { } using the Scanner class to take user input.
